.TH CAIGED-BUILD 1 "February 2026" "caiged" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
caiged-build \- Build the base and spin container images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B caiged build
\fIworkdir\fR [\fIflags\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B caiged build
builds the Docker images required for running caiged containers. This includes:
.IP \(bu 2
The base image containing common dependencies and tools
.IP \(bu 2
The spin-specific image with additional configuration
.PP
Building is normally automatic when you run
.BR caiged ,
but this command allows you to pre-build images or rebuild them explicitly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-spin \fIname\fR
Spin name to build (default: "qa").
.TP
.B \-\-repo \fIpath\fR
Path to caiged repository containing spins/Dockerfile/entrypoint.sh.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Build images for the default spin:
.B caiged build .
.TP
Build images for a specific spin:
.B caiged build . \-\-spin dev
.TP
Build using a custom caiged repository:
.B caiged build . \-\-repo /path/to/caiged
.SH IMAGE NAMES
Images are tagged as:
.IP \(bu 2
Base image: \fBcaiged-base\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Spin image: \fBcaiged-{spin}\fR (e.g., caiged-qa, caiged-dev)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR caiged (1),
.BR docker (1)
